<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLASS-SIZE (San Francisco) _ Despite a push to cut class size,
California ranks dead last among states in the number of teachers,
counselors and librarians per pupil, according to a study released
Friday. By JULIAN GUTHRIE.
</P>
<P>
   HIV-GENE (San Francisco) _ Between 7 and 13 percent of people
may carry a genetic variation that helps HIV along its deadly path,
speeding its progression to full-blown AIDS by as much as five
years, researchers have found. By ULYSSES TORASSA.
</P>
<P>
   SF-QUAKE (San Francisco) _ A moderate earthquake thumped much of
the Bay Area awake early Friday, stopping BART on its tracks and
setting off dozens of burglar alarms. No injuries and only minor
household damage were reported from the temblor, which the U.S.
Geological Survey in Menlo Park said measured 4.1 and was centered
on the Hayward Fault. By LARRY D. HATFIELD.
</P>
<P>
   411-CHARGES (San Francisco) _ Pacific Bell's proposal to double
what it charges for 411 directory assistance calls drew angry
comments from several Bay Area consumer and special interest
groups. By WENDY TANAKA.
</P>
