computers _ one thin and light, one bulky but with the biggest
screen available on a portable. By DWIGHT SILVERMAN.
</P>
<P>
   With: COMPUTER-HELPLINE
</P>
<P>
   SF-BANKING (San Francisco) _ Top city officials are discussing
whether San Francisco should sever its long-standing relationship
with BankAmerica, following concern over the apparent corporate
culture clash resulting from the bank's recent merger with North
Carolina-based NationsBank. The officials say that an unfamiliar
management style at the bank now headquartered in Charlotte, N.C.,
appears insensitive to San Francisco tradition, culture and
diversity.By GEORGE RAINE.
</P>
