   LIFESTYLE/FEATURES (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HIV-BROWNIE (Queensbury, N.Y.) _ Quashawn Donovan, 8, has been
placed with a Queensbury Brownie troop after being denied admission
to several troops last month because she is HIV positive. The
Adirondack Girl Scout Council recently held a training session to
help educated troop leaders about the virus that can lead to AIDS.
By LINDA TRISCHITTA.
</P>
<P>
   HOLIDAY-LIGHTS (Albany, N.Y.) _ Festive lighting adds so much to
the home around the holidays. But care should be used when buying
holiday electrical lights. Last year there was a major national
recall of more than 1.5 million sets of curtain-style,
indoor/outdoor holiday lights, more commonly known as icicle
lights. By FRANCES INGRAHAM. (For release Sunday, Dec. 6)
