   PINOCHET (San Francisco) _ Before he got on the plane to London,
former Chilean dictator Augusto Pinochet should have checked who
was running the new British administration. He would have found
that the three top senior cabinet posts _ the finance, foreign and
defense ministers _ all cut their ideological teeth in the Scottish
Labor Party of the '70s. Back then, these young activists, now
government ministers, were radical. By ALAN BLACK.
