<SLUG> BC-SF-QUAKE-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MODERATE QUAKE HITS BAY AREA 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By LARRY D. HATFIELD  
 c.1998 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ A moderate earthquake thumped the San Francisco
Bay Area early Friday, halting commuter trains and setting off
dozens of burglar alarms.
</P>
<P>
   No injuries and only minor household damage were reported from
the quake, which the U.S. Geological Survey said measured 4.1 on
the Richter scale and was centered 3 to 3 1/2 miles southeast of
Richmond on the Hayward Fault.
</P>
<P>
   The jolt was felt throughout the region at 4:16 a.m. It was
described variously as a thump, sounding like a train or rocks
thrown on the roof.
</P>
<P>
   Callers to radio and police stations said the shaking lasted for
only a few seconds but, depending on where they were, the
evaluations of the intensity ranged from violent to mild.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a major, major jolt,'' said Marie Griffith, an aide at
the Ellens Memorial Hospital, a small retirement home in Richmond.
``It shook up everyone.''
</P>
<P>
   Toll takers at the Golden Gate Bridge said they did not feel it.
</P>
<P>
   At the Richmond-San Rafael Bridge, Sgt. Mary Ellen Tieger said
the span suffered no apparent damage, but bridge workers were
shaken.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was one hard jolt,'' she said. ``It wasn't even a shake. It
felt like someone dropped the floor under your feet.''
</P>
<P>
   USGS spokeswoman Pat Jorgenson said the quake awakened her in
her Menlo Park apartment, but was not alarming.
</P>
<P>
   The quake interrupted power to commuter trains on the Richmond
line for more than 30 minutes. All Bay Area Rapid Transit trains
were stopped for a track and facilities inspection after the quake,
but BART spokesman Mike Healy said no damage was found.
</P>
<P>
   BART trains were traveling at reduced speeds, as is customary
after an earthquake.
</P>
<P>
   At the Emeryville Police Department, a few miles from Richmond,
dispatcher Maria Bell said she did get a few calls, but only for
information.
</P>
<P>
   ``It scared me,'' she said. ``It shook pretty good.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-04-98 1414EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19981204.0174 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-04 14:20 </DATE_TIME>
