handheld computer. Using the right software, thieves can copy the
codes from infrared controls used for locking car doors. By Duncan
Graham-Rowe. 500 words. (slugged:
BC-COMPUTERS-AND-CRIME-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL;
</P>
