<P>
   &UR; RADIATION AFFECTS NEIGHBORING CELLS &LR;  _ Scientists in Boston
have found that targeting low-level radiation on human cells causes
changes in levels of gene activity in neighboring cells. It is
possible that this bystander effect might be a mechanism to
minimize cell damage. By Rob Edwards. 500 words (slugged:
BC-RADIATION-AND-HUMAN-CELLS-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL;
</P>
