   &UR; COULD A NASAL VACCINE FINALLY PUT AN END TO THE BLACK DEATH? &LR;  _
Nose drops based on a new vaccine can protect mice from bubonic
plague, say researchers at the University of Birmingham in England.
If clinical trials on humans are successful, it may allay fears of
a worldwide pandemic started by antibiotic-resistant plague
bacteria. By Debora MacKenzie. 500 words. (slugged:
BC-STOPPING-THE-BUBONIC-PLAGUE-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL;
