<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BORDERS-COLUMN05-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Did you hear the one about the 3 guys ...
 &HT;    By Gary Borders
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are a few jokes I've been saving up for a slow holiday week
just like
</P>
<P>
   this:
</P>
<P>
   _Three men show up at St. Peter's gate at the same time. St.
Peter figures heaven is getting a bit crowded, and he tells the
trio to describe to him how they died. The one who died the most
horrible death would be admitted to heaven.
</P>
<P>
   The first man starts.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have long long suspected that my wife was being unfaithful
to me, but I'd never been able to catch her. So today I left work
early and went home. Sure enough, my wife was lying naked in the
bed. I looked around and found this man, wearing only gym shorts,
hanging from our balcony. We live on the 25th floor.
</P>
<P>
   ``In a rage, I began stomping on his hands until he had to let
go. He fell 25 floors and landed in some bushes. It didn't even
hurt him!
</P>
<P>
   ``In a rage, I picked up a refrigerator and chunked it over the
balcony. It landed on the man and killed him. But that's when I had
the heart attack from all the exertion and died.''
</P>
<P>
   St. Peter agreed that was a pretty horrible story.
</P>
<P>
   It was the next man's turn.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was doing my exercises on the balcony of my 26-floor
apartment, as I do every afternoon. I somehow slipped and tumbled
over the railing but luckily grabbed hold of the railing on the
balcony below. That's when this maniac comes charging out there and
begins stomping on my hands and cursing. Finally, I had to let go.
Miraculously, I landed in some bushes and wasn't even hurt.
</P>
<P>
   ``Then that maniac heaved a refrigerator over the side of the
balcony, and it landed on me and killed me.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Whew,'' St. Peter said. ``What a way to go.''
</P>
<P>
   The third man spoke up.
</P>
<P>
   ``Picture this. I'm hiding naked in a refrigerator.''
</P>
<P>
   _Two guys come across a big hole in the ground.
</P>
<P>
   ``Reckon how deep that hole is?'' one asks the other. One man
tosses a rock into the hole and waits to hear the sound of it
landing. He hears nothing.
</P>
<P>
   His partner tosses a bigger rock into the hole. Again, both
listen but hear nothing.
</P>
<P>
   A railroad tie is nearby. The two men walk over, pick it up and
toss it in the hole. A few seconds later a goat comes flying by and
leaps into the hole.
</P>
<P>
   ``Did you see that?'' one man says. ``Reckon why that goat
jumped into that hole?''
</P>
<P>
   A little while later, while they're still pondering all this, a
farmer walks up and asks if they've seen a goat.
</P>
<P>
   ``Well, we saw one come running by and jump into this here
hole,'' one man replies.
</P>
<P>
   The farmer shakes his head. ``That can't be my goat. Mine was
tied to a railroad tie.''
</P>
<P>
   In honor of the game between Texas and Texas A&AMP;M, here are a
trio of Aggie
</P>
<P>
   jokes.
</P>
<P>
   _A University of Texas grad, a Baylor alumnus, and an Aggie had
all committed horrendous crimes and were going to be shot. The
Teasip was brought up and blindfolded. The general shouted,
``Ready, aim ...'' and the Teasip guy yelled, ``Hurricane!,''
everybody ducked, and he ran away free.
</P>
<P>
   Dismayed at losing their first prisoner, the guards brought up
the Baylor student with renewed vigor. They blindfolded him and the
general commanded,
</P>
<P>
   ``Ready, aim...'' and the Baylor guy shouted, ``Tornado!''
Fearing for their lives, everybody ducked, and he ran away free.
</P>
<P>
   Well, the Aggie has been watching all this and starts thinking,
``They all yelled natural disasters and they got away, so I will
too.''
</P>
<P>
   So they brought him up and blinded folded him, the general
shouted, ``Ready, aim...'' and the Aggie screamed, ``Fire!!''
</P>
<P>
   _An Aggie and a Longhorn are in hell. The Longhorn is chained to
an ugly old woman, and the Aggie is chained to Pamela Anderson. The
devil comes in and tells the two unfortunate souls that they will
be in this situation for eternity.
</P>
<P>
   The Longhorn asks the devil why he is chained to the ugly old
woman. The devil replies, ``This is your punishment for being so
mean to all those Aggies over the years.''
</P>
<P>
   The Longhorn then asks, ``If this is hell, why does the Aggie
get to be chained to Pamela Anderson''?
</P>
<P>
   To which the devil replies, ``That's Pamela Anderson's
punishment''!
</P>
<P>
   _An Aggie and a Longhorn are watching the news on TV. There's a
film story about a girl on the ledge of a building threatening to
commit suicide. The police were trying to talk her down when the
Longhorn says to the Aggie, ``I'll bet you five dollars that she
jumps.'' The Aggie took the bet.
</P>
<P>
   Seconds later, the girl jumps. The Aggie takes five dollars from
his pocket and hands it to the Longhorn. The Longhorn says, ``I
can't take your money. I saw the same film clip on the 6 p.m. news
today and knew she was going to jump.''
</P>
<P>
   The Aggie says, ``I watched it, too, but I didn't think she
would do it a second time.''
</P>
<P>
   Gary Borders is editor and publisher of The Nacogdoches Daily
Sentinel. His
</P>
<P>
   e-mail address is gborders(at)coxnews.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
