   MARKETING-TOYS _ATLANTA _ Kids play a big part in influencing
family spending, to the tune of $150 billion a year. Everything
from cereal, toys, tvs, cars and even family vacation destinations.
Marketing to children becomes a very complex and sophisticated
communication process. Parents may also come to realize that the
marketplace is an important agent for socialization of children's
culture as much as, or more so, than schools and parents. How do
marketing firms design ads that get kids to put pressure on their
parents to purchase certain items? And how do parents feel about
this pressure on kids for consumerism? (Brraddock/Poole, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
