   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   FBC_BCSBCS _ ATLANTA _ Could Tennessee beat Mississippi State to
win the SEC title and fall out of the Fiesta Bowl championship
game? Only the top two teams in the BCS rankings will advance to
the Fiesta Bowl and play for the national title. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) FOR SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   FBC-TENN-FULMER _ Tennessee coach Phillip Fulmer has received
his share of criticism over the years, especially during the years
the Vols were annual losers to Florida, but is leading one of the
most successful college football programs in the country. Tennessee
has won 10 games in five of his six seasons as head coach, won the
SEC championship last season and is favored to win another title
tonight against Mississippi State. For all of his success, Fulmer
still hasn't received the credit of more popular coaches Steve
Spurrier and Bobby Bowden. Maybe part of it is that those coaches
have something Fulmer doesn't _ a national championship.
(Wilkinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) FOR SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   FBC-MSTATE-SHERRILL _ Jackie Sherrill has had success at each of
his coaching stops, including Pittsburgh, Texas A&AMP;M and Mississippi
State. But controversy always seems to swirl around Sherrill, whose
Texas A&AMP;M program was put on probation by the NCAA after his
departure and who had a bull castrated on the practice field at
Mississippi State in 1992. Despite the controversy, Sherrill has
been successful and leads Mississippi State in search of its first
SEC championship since 1941. (Parker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
FOR SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   FBC-HUMMER-COLUMN _ On the SEC Championship game. (Hummer,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) FOR SATURDAY
</P>
