<P>
   FBC-RICKY-CHANCE _ AUSTIN, Texas _ University of Texas running
back Ricky Williams will be going to New York for the Heisman
Trophy ceremony next week. He'll be joined by Kentucky quarterback
Tim Couch and likely Kansas State quarterback Michael Bishop. After
winning the Walter Camp Award Monday, Williams will likely be the
Heisman winner also because only five times in the past 30 years
has the Walter Camp Award winner not won the Heisman. (Wangrin,
Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   BOX-LENNOX _ Despite a 34-1 record and partial ownership of the
heavyweight title, Lennox Lewis has had little following in the
U.S. and has never done much to inspire excitement in the division.
He is a big guy with possibly the division's best right hand, but
is known more for the opponents he hasn't fought. By meeting
Holyfield in March, he has a chance to gain some respect and,
maybe, fans. (Schultz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
