   FILM-REDGRAVE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DALLAS _ The woman looks, well, severe: scowling face, hunched
shoulders, quick-shuffling walk, Hungarian accent that seems
designed to make the horses whinny. She doesn't match the other
woman: tall, refined, casually elegant in a beige pantsuit,
speaking with a British accent as soothing as a kitten's purr.
They're the same woman: Lynn Redgrave as Hanna the housekeeper in
``Gods and Monsters,'' the newly opened acclaimed movie; and Lynn
Redgrave the actress, gently complaining about the lack of heat in
Dallas' Inwood pub. By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
