<P>
   UNDATED _ A ``voice in the wilderness'' writes to Dr. Bombay:
``The real story on computers these days is in the way the
software/hardware folks are forcing users to replace satisfactory
equipment. Examples: I was using TurboTax for years on DOS. All of
a sudden TurboTax only runs on Windows. I was using Juno for E-mail
with a 386 motherboard. All of a sudden Juno will not run on less
than a 486. My Print Shop files will not transfer to the new model.
You get the picture. By DR. EMILIO BOMBAY. Story has moved in ``l''
lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
