   CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Chrysler may have defined the minivan with its highly
successful products, but General Motors conceded a huge share of
the market by rolling out its futuristic ``Dustbuster''-looking
models in 1990. After virtually ignoring the minivan phenomenon for
six years, then coming out with such a controversial product, GM
allowed Chrysler to gain a strong position as minivan market
leader. By G. CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III. Story will move in ``l''
lifestyle category. &QL; 
