. 
The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Jimmy
Johnson at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
PSYCHO-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ Gus Van Sant's pathologically
faithful remake of Alfred Hitchcock's classic ``Psycho'' is an
interesting, respectful, even quite playful formal exercise. But
like the academic effort it very much is, the film is mainly good
for imparting the kinds of lessons succeeding generations of
filmgoers never seem to learn. By Bob Strauss. 
. 
DIGITAL-TECH (Los Angeles) _Just in time for Christmas, Esther
Dyson has updated her book about life in the digital age, and what
it means for even those of us who aren't technologically bent. The
update is appropriately called Release 2.1, following the same
version-numbering conventions used for software updates. By David
Bloom. 
. 
TONY-BOOK (Los Angeles) _ Tony Bennett has thought about writing
his life story from time to time during his 50 years in show
business. But the stories Bennett wanted to tell _ memories of his
loving family, tales from the recording studio and thousands of
concert appearances, lessons learned from friends famous and
otherwise _ didn't interest most publishers. By Glenn Whipp. 
. 
The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``l'' lifestyle news file. For questions, contact Jimmy Johnson
at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
TREES-DECORATION (Los Angeles) _ If you were rich and famous, how
would you decorate your Christmas tree? Here's a sneak peek at some
inspiration, as celebrities decorate (or have someone decorate)
Christmas trees as part of the fifth annual Christmas Tree Lane at
the Beverly Hilton hotel. The trees will be auctioned off starting
Dec. 7, with money to benefit charities. By Carol Bidwell. 
. 

