<P>
   CLINTON-SCANDAL (Washington) _ The House Judiciary Committee,
focusing on President Clinton's conduct in the Monica Lewinsky
affair, agrees to allow the White House to review evidence of
potentially impeachable acts committed by Clinton. By JOHN HENRY.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACHMENT-SCHUMER (Colonie, N.Y.) _ Rep. Charles E. Schumer, a
member of the House Judiciary Committee that is investigating
President Clinton, says he's ``really worried'' that the House will
vote to impeach the president for lying about his affair with
Monica Lewinsky. Schumer blames ``radical right'' Republicans for
manipulating the impeachment process. By JAMES M. ODATO.
</P>
<P>
   SHUTTLE-LAUNCH (Cape Canaveral, Fla.) _ The shuttle Endeavour
soars into orbit, its six American and Russian crew members eager
to assemble the first components of the new international space
station. By MARK CARREAU. (Already filed.)
