<HEADLINE>
1999 OLDSMOBILE SILHOUETTE PREMIERE MINIVAN
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   At A Glance:
</P>
<P>
   The Package: Top-of-the-line, premium five-door,
seven-passenger, V-6 powered, front-drive minivan with leather
interior and special audio/video package.
</P>
<P>
   Highlights: Perhaps the most impressive minivan every built,
this vehicle has lots of room for people and cargo, with loads of
luxury, including leather interior and a videocassette player and
pop-down LCD screen to keep the kids occupied. There is lots of
power and the ride is smooth and quiet.
</P>
<P>
   Negatives: Video player is down on the floor at the driver's
feet, with controls that are hard to reach while driving; some of
the other gadgetry is confusing and inconvenient to operate..
</P>
<P>
   Major competitors: Chrysler Town &AMP; Country/Dodge Grand Caravan
LE, Mercury Villager/Nissan Quest, Ford Windstar, Toyota Sienna
XLE, Honda Odyssey. EPA fuel economy: 18 miles per gallon city, 25
highway.
</P>
<P>
   Base price: $30,605 plus $570 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   Price as tested: $31,175, including transportation.
</P>
<P>
   On The Road rating: A-plus.
</P>
