<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-SANDERS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS' SANDERS LIKELY WON'T PLAY AGAINST SAINTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Cowboys cornerback Deion Sanders did not
practice yesterday, all but assuring he will not play against the
New Orleans Saints tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys coach Chan Gailey, who earlier in the week said Sanders
would not play if he couldn't practice on the sprained toe by
yesterday, said he intends to follow through with his plans to hold
Sanders out a second consecutive game.
</P>
<P>
   ``Never say never, but it looks like he's not going to play,''
Gailey said.
</P>
<P>
   Although Sanders has shown improvement and walks without a limp,
Gailey said the Cowboys would rather play it conservatively and let
the injury heal fully, rather than chance a recurring problem.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a gray area,'' Gailey said. ``There are several factors.
Do we want him to get closer to 100 percent? Yes, we do. Can he
play? Probably, but will he be set back again?''
</P>
<P>
   With Kevin Smith also sidelined with a strained back, the
Cowboys will go with Charlie Williams and Kevin Mathis as starting
cornerbacks. Larry Brown, signed Wednesday, will be the primary
backup and serve as a nickel cornerback.
</P>
<P>
   Mathis, who has missed the past three games with a fractured
right forearm, said he's excited to get back on the field and
doesn't anticipate having any problems playing with a cast on his
right arm.
Offense to lend a hand
</P>
<P>
   Gailey understands his defensive patchwork will be a weakness
against the Saints, but he'd rather concentrate on the Cowboys'
strength _ their offense.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys' offense is ranked fourth in the league and has
scored at least 30 points in four of the past five games. The
Saints' defense ranks 27th.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our offense has been playing well,'' Gailey said. ``If we can
continue the things we are doing, we can help the defense.''
Briefly
</P>
<P>
   Recently signed Tyrone Hughes is expected to return kickoffs and
punts against the Saints.
</P>
<P>
   Running back Chris Warren will miss tomorrow's game with a
strained groin. Sherman Williams will step in as the third-down
running back.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
