</P>
<P>
   In Miami, No. 3 UCLA (10-0) faces the Hurricanes (7-3), who are
coming off a 66-13 shellacking at Syracuse. This game was postponed
from Sept. 26 because of Hurricane Georges. A UCLA victory would
keep the Bruins in the national-title picture.
</P>
<P>
   ``You've got to get excited about the chance to spoil their
hopes for the national championship,'' Miami linebacker Dan Morgan
said. ``I think everyone's feeling real good about the
opportunity.''
</P>
<P>
   If Kansas State, Tennessee and UCLA all win, there will be
considerable drama Sunday afternoon when the final BCS rankings are
announced. The three teams were separated by 1.32 points in this
week's rankings. The top two teams in the final listings will play
in the Fiesta Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   If there are no upsets today, it will be up to the 142 voters in
the media and coaches polls, plus the computer programs to decide
the top two teams. At least two of the coaches involved felt the
need to lobby.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've got to understand it's a one-game tournament now for
us,'' UCLA coach Bob Toledo said. ``If we lose, we're out. It would
be a real shame to get this far and not take advantage of it. I
think our players will be real focused.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'd be very, very disappointed if we go undefeated and don't
play in the Fiesta Bowl. I honestly, truly believe we should be one
of the top two teams playing in the Fiesta Bowl if we win
\Rtoday\S.''
</P>
<P>
   Tennessee coach Phillip Fulmer also felt the urge to campaign
for his team.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've beaten four of the Top 25 \RFlorida, Georgia, Arkansas
and Syracuse\S, and three of those teams were in the Top 10 when we
played them,'' he said. ``But more than that, I just think that if
you're the SEC champion and you're 12-0, you have got to be in the
big game.''
</P>
<P>
   Also on tap today: The Western Athletic Conference championship
game and the annual Army-Navy clash. The WAC game will be the last
title game in the short lifespan of the 16-team conference.
However, the BYU-Air Force contest in Las Vegas will do no more
than determine a champion; both teams have accepted bowl bids (Air
Force to one of the Hawaii games, BYU to the Liberty).
</P>
<P>
   Of the 22 bowl games, seven have their teams set. The other 15
will find out their matchups tomorrow based on the results in St.
Louis, Atlanta and Miami.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
